work.p: This prose manuscript includes the line "Which is the poem or any book that is not diseased?" which appeared in a slightly altered form in "Poem of Many in One" in 1856: "Which is the theory or book that is not diseased?" (p. 181). The poem, eventually titled "By Blue Ontario's Shore," was retained through subsequent editions of Leaves, although the line was dropped after 1860–1861.

body.p: Of Health does not tell any more in the body, than it tells does in literature.—Which is the poem, or any book, that is not diseased?—(If perfect health appear in a poem, or any book, it surely propogatespropagates itself while many nations rise a great while.) Show perfect health and native qualities, and that which possesses them and you are welcome to all the rest.—
